"title": "8218: consecration",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8218: consecration",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The setting apart of people, things, times or places as sacred, for God to use.</p>\n<h2>Consecration is the requirement of a holy God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:7-Lev20:8\">LEV 20:7–20:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:44\">LEV 11:44</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev22:32\">LEV 22:32</a></p>\n<h2>The consecration of people</h2>\n<h3>The importance of personal consecration</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:13\">ROM 6:13</a></p>\n<h3>Inward consecration to God is symbolised by outward cleansing</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:1\">ROM 12:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:14-2Cor5:15\">2CO 5:14–5:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:24\">1PE 2:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:10\">EXO 19:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:14\">EXO 19:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:5\">1SA 16:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr30:17\">2CH 30:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr35:6\">2CH 35:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps50:5\">PSA 50:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:1\">ROM 12:1</a></p>\n<h3>The consecration of all firstborn males</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod13:2\">EXO 13:2</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:22-Luke2:23\">LUK 2:22–2:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod13:12-Exod13:13\">EXO 13:12–13:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num3:11-Num3:13\">NUM 3:11–3:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num8:17-Num8:18\">NUM 8:17–8:18</a> <em>The Levites served in place of the firstborn males in Israel.</em></p>\n<h3>The consecration of priests</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:1\">EXO 29:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:22\">EXO 19:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs13:33\">1KI 13:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr30:3\">2CH 30:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr30:24\">2CH 30:24</a></p>\n<h3>The consecration of the Aaronic priesthood</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:30\">EXO 30:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:41\">EXO 28:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:30\">LEV 8:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr23:13\">1CH 23:13</a></p>\n<h3>The consecration of the Levitical priesthood</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr15:12\">1CH 15:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr23:6\">2CH 23:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr29:5\">2CH 29:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr35:3\">2CH 35:3</a></p>\n<h3>Special consecration is marked by a vow</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:8\">NUM 6:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:11\">NUM 6:11</a> <em>the Nazirite vow</em></p>\n<h2>The consecration of things</h2>\n<h3>Altars</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:36-Exod29:37\">EXO 29:36–29:37</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:29\">EXO 30:29</a>EXO <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:9-Exod40:11\">40:9–40:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:11-Lev8:12\">LEV 8:11–8:12</a></p>\n<h3>Offerings</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:38\">EXO 28:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:27\">EXO 29:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev22:2\">LEV 22:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr30:17\">2CH 30:17</a></p>\n<h3>Garments</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:3\">EXO 28:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:21\">EXO 29:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:13\">EXO 40:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:39-Num15:40\">NUM 15:39–15:40</a></p>\n<h3>Bread</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam21:4\">1SA 21:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam21:6\">1SA 21:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:4\">MAT 12:4</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:25-Mark2:26\">MRK 2:25–2:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:3-Luke6:4\">LUK 6:3–6:4</a></p>\n<h3>Meat</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag2:12\">HAG 2:12</a> <em>The state of consecration could be transmitted</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer11:15\">JER 11:15</a> <em>True consecration should involve a right spirit.</em></p>\n<h2>Certain places are consecrated</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:23\">EXO 19:23</a> <em>Mount Sinai</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:43-Exod29:44\">EXO 29:43–29:44</a> <em>the Tent of Meeting</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:10\">LEV 8:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num7:1\">NUM 7:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:64\">1KI 8:64</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr7:7\">2CH 7:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs9:3\">1KI 9:3</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr7:16\">2CH 7:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr29:17-2Chr29:19\">2CH 29:17–29:19</a></p>\n<h2>Certain times are specially consecrated</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:10\">LEV 25:10</a> <em>the Year of Jubilee</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:3\">GEN 2:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:8\">EXO 20:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:11\">EXO 20:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:12\">DEU 5:12</a></p>\n<h2>The consecration of daily life</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:4-1Tim4:5\">1TI 4:4–4:5</a></strong> <em>The reference may be to grace before eating.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech14:20-Zech14:21\">ZEC 14:20–14:21</a></p>\n<h2>Consecration as preparation for work and worship</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:18\">NUM 11:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh3:5\">JOS 3:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:13\">JOS 7:13</a></p>\n<h2>Consecration to other gods incurs God's displeasure</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa66:17\">ISA 66:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg17:3\">JDG 17:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr13:9\">2CH 13:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr26:18\">2CH 26:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr30:17\">2CH 30:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:14\">2CH 36:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos9:10\">HOS 9:10</a></p>",
